          "date": "2013-10-17 00:24:16.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-2456 lnet: DLC user space Configuration utility",
        "message": "LU-2456 lnet: DLC user space Configuration utility\n\nThis is the sixth patch of a set of patches that enables DLC.\n\nThis patch adds a configuration utility, lcmd (lustre cmd),\nwhich provides a way for sys admins to configure LNET\nparameters.  This utility has been added to the /lustre/utils\ndirectory because it is anticipated that it will be used\nin the future to configure other non LNET parameters.\n\nThis utility brings in an infrastructure for command\nparsing based on YAML command description.  The command\ndescription file will describe the syntax of each command\nand which function to call when each command is matched\n\nThe utility uses readline library as its backbone. Therefore,\nthe library must be installed on the system running lcmd\n\nThe lcmd utility can be started with multiple command line\nparameters including, the location of the library to\nhandle commands, the location of the file that describes\nthe commands.  This makes the infrastructure flexible to\nbe used by any command line utility.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I598b1ee1a4f6883ea9c99fcb0db72a52e6f2d9f6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
